An '''Employer Reference Number''' ('''ERN''') or '''Employer [[PAYE]] Reference''' is a unique reference number issued in the UK by [[HMRC]] to an employer.<ref>HMRC, [https://www.tax.service.gov.uk/information/help?helpcategory=security&affinitygroup=&helpid=EmployerPAYEreference Employer PAYE reference], accessed 6 October 2017</ref> Every organisation operating a Pay as you Earn (PAYE) schene is allocated an ERN, a unique set of letters and numbers used by HMRC (and others) to identify each employer, consisting of a three-digit HMRC office number and a reference number unique to each business.<ref>Simply Business, [https://www.simplybusiness.co.uk/knowledge/articles/2010/07/2010-07-28-employer-reference-numbers-vital-information-for-business-owners/ Employer Reference Numbers – vital information for business owners], 28 July 2010, accessed 3 October 2017</ref>

The [[Financial Conduct Authority]] (FCA), which regulates [[Insurance Company|insurance companies]] in the UK, requires insurers and [[Insurance broker|broker]]s to obtain the ERN from clients whom they are insuring or for whom they are arranging insurance for Employers' Liability, and to state the ERN in their Employers' Liability Register.<ref>Financial Conduct Authority, [https://handbook.fca.org.uk/handbook/ICOBS/8/Annex1.html ICOBS 8 Annex 1 Employers' Liability Register], accessed 5 October 2017</ref> ERN's are also used by the Employers' Liability Tracing Office, an independent industry body recognized by the FCA,<ref>Allianz Insurance, [https://www.allianzebroker.co.uk/content/allianzebroker/en_gb/application/content/documents/broker-support/registration-databases/ELTO/elto-fact-sheet/_jcr_content/documentProperties/currentDocument.res/acom6404-1.pdf Employers’ Liability Tracing Office (ELTO)], accessed 6 October 2017</ref> who can assist employees to find their former employer's Employers' Liability Insurance provider if they need to make a claim for injury or illness incurred at work.<ref>[https://www.mortonmichel.com/Site/Uploads/Documents/_resources/_downloads/ELTO_Technical_update_Morton_Michel_03_2013.pdf Employer Liability Reference (ERN) – Information for Policyholders], accessed 6 October 2017</ref>

