{{Infobox person | name = Ennio Doris | image = Ennio Doris UFFICIALE nospilla.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1940|7|3|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Tombolo]], Italy | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | residence = Tombolo, Italy | nationality = Italian | education = | occupation = Businessman | known for = | home_town = | salary = | networth = US$2.5 billion (September 2018)<ref name="Forbes profile">{{cite web |title=Forbes profile: Ennio Doris & family |url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/ennio-doris/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=28 September 2018}}</ref> | title = Chairman, [[Banca Mediolanum]]<ref name="Forbes profile"/> | term = | predecessor = | successor = | boards = | spouse = Married | children = 2 | parents = | relatives = | website = }}
'''Ennio Doris''' (born 3 July 1940), is an Italian [[billionaire]] businessman, the founder of Mediolanum SpA, and chairman of [[Banca Mediolanum]], part of [[Gruppo Mediolanum]], a large Italian banking, funds management and insurance group.<ref name="Ibpus.comUSA2012">{{cite book|title=Italy Country Study Guide: Strategic Information and Developments|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1XAs34Terl8C&pg=PA162|accessdate=5 October 2014|year=2012|publisher=Int'l Business Publications|isbn=9781438774664|page=162}}</ref>
==Early life== He was born in Tombolo, a small village near [[Padova]], Italy on 3 July 1940.{{fact|date=September 2018}}
==Career== Doris entered the retail asset management field in 1969 when he became a salesman for Fideuram. In 1971 he joined Dival, where he rose to be the head of a 700-person sales force. In 1982 he started his own company "Programma Italia" and convinced [[Silvio Berlusconi]] to invest 250,000 Euro in return for a half share of the company. His strategy was to focus on retail client relationships, while subcontracting the management of invested funds to other firms. Under his charismatic leadership his network of salesmen grew rapidly as did the funds under management. He added insurance and banking and renamed the firm Mediolanum. In June 1996 the company was floated on the Italian stock market. Berlusconi described it as the best investment he had ever made.{{fact|date=September 2018}}
==Personal life== Doris is married, with two children, and lives in [[Tombolo]], Italy.<ref name="Forbes profile"/> His son, Massimo Doris, is the CEO of [[Banca Mediolanum]].<ref name="Forbes profile"/>
Doris owns the 197-foot sailing yacht ''Seven''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/monaco-yacht-show-billionaire-yachts-photos-2018-9|title=9 outrageous yachts appearing at the Monaco Yacht Show owned by some of the world's richest billionaires|author=|date=|website=businessinsider.com|accessdate=28 September 2018}}</ref>
